.SH NAME
cmat_new_alloc \- create a matrix and specify the maximum dimensions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fB#include <it/mat.h>
.sp
cmat cmat_new_alloc ( size_t h, size_t w, size_t hmax, size_t wmax
);
\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The function \fBcmat_new_alloc\fR creates a matrix of size \fIh\fRx\fIw\fR, but allocate the memory for a matrix of size \fIhmax\fRx\fIwmax\fR\&. This will allow the matrix to grow up to this size without any re-allocation of the matrix.  
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.PP
The new matrix
.SH "EXAMPLE"

.nf

#include <mat.h>

\&...

cmat m = cmat_new_alloc (1,2,3,4);   /* m of size 1x2  */

int h  = cmat_height (m);            /* h = 1          */
int w  = cmat_width (m);             /* w = 2          */
int hm = cmat_height_max (m);        /* hm = 3         */
int wm = cmat_width_max (m);         /* wm = 4         */
.fi
